 'SCOPE: Drone strikes have occurred in Pakistan, Yemen, Somalia, Libya, Syria, and Iraq. Many countries where the U.S. is not at war. Thousands killed.',
 'SIGNATURE STRIKES: Strikes based on"patterns of behavior"rather than known identity. Military-age males in certain areas automatically counted as militants.',
 'AMERICAN CITIZENS: Anwar al-Awlaki was killed by drone in 2011 without trial. Two weeks later, his 16-year-old son was killed. His 8-year-old daughter was killed in a 2017 raid.',
 'CIVILIAN DEATHS: The Bureau of Investigative Journalism documents hundreds of civilian casualties including children. Official counts dramatically understate deaths.',
 'DOUBLE TAP: Pattern of striking the same area twice, killing first responders and rescuers. Documented by human rights groups.',
 'LEGAL QUESTIONS: The program operates under secret legal memos. Congress has not declared war on countries being struck. Constitutional lawyers call it assassination.',
